From Gordon Banks Subject Re ORGAN DONATION AND TRANSPLANTATION FACT SHEET In article writes My wife cannot donate blood because she has been to a malarial region in the past three In fact she tried to have her bone marrow typed and they wouldn't even do that Why The FDA I Rules say no blood or blood products donations from anyone who has been in a malarial area for I was a platelet donor until my Thailand trip and my blood bank was very disappointed to find out they couldn't use me for When the secretary of state asked me if I wanted to donate my organs I said no because I figured that no one would want them given my Was I correct Not The same rules may not apply to organ donation as to blood In fact I'm sure they don' Gordon Banks Skepticism is the chastity of the intellect and it is shameful to surrender it too